Let’s talk about aftercare

One of my highly asked questions is “is this going to damage my lashes if I do it for a long time?” 

Now listen, lash lifts are an amazing service but WE ARE DOING A CHEMICAL PROCESS. 
🫴🏼✨Aftercare IS Necessary 

Think about a time you ran out of conditioner…. How did your hair feel after that shower? Dry? Crunchy? Squeaky? It’s the same with lashes. 

This client had her first lash lift December 29th and came back 8 weeks later and her lashes still had most of the curl. When you apply a conditioner like LASH SURGE everyday it keeps the hair hydrated which helps the grow out process and allows you to continuously get lash lifts. I’ve had clients for 5 years who come around every 2 months with no problem. It’s because they follow proper aftercare. I stress this SOOO much which is why I include a LASH SURGE in every clients first appointment. 

If my client comes in with 70% (eyeballing this) or more curl left from the previous lift I have them come back in. 

SWIPE ➡️ to see the clients after 2 weeks later

‼️Spot the difference‼️

I’d like you to comment the difference in this photo I will be posting a video in my subscription group on why the slight difference in this photo makes a BIG DIFFERENCE in the outcome of your lash lifts!

WE GOT IT

Let’s talk 🗣️ 
• Naturally Curled Lashes •

At first glance it looks like this client may have over processed lashes but these are just naturally curly, she hasn’t had a lift in over a year! 

The problem ❌
Overly curled lashes make it hard to apply mascara and hide how long this clients lashes actually are

The solution ✅ 
Stretch those lashes to enhance their length and redefine her eyes

Lash lifts are an incredible technique designed to uplift and define your lashes, giving them a stunning, natural-looking lift. Even if you were blessed with gorgeously curly lashes, a lash lift can take your lash game to the next level 📈

I specifically used a rod for these lashes. Traditionally I’d pull a large for the length but because the goal was to loosen the curl and not create more of one, I used an XXL rod. 

The Result ⚡️ 
Long gorgeous lashes that are more manageable

Lash lifts can be customized to suit your unique specific needs and curl preference, whether you're looking for a subtle enhancement or a bold, dramatic lift.

In today's world, where social media has become a powerful tool for amplifying voices, it is crucial to use it for a good cause. As an advocate for ethical business practices in the skincare industry, I want to take a moment to shed light on a movement that affects not only my friends and followers but also most estheticians.

The issue ‼️
There is an increasing number of skincare companies that require medical directors to purchase their products, even though these products are NOT medical-grade products. These companies also hold bias toward estheticians with large followings, “By passing” the need for a medical director to capitalize on the reach they have to smaller esthies. 

It is disheartening to see how these companies take advantage of estheticians by forcing them to hire a medical director to bring on their line. All the while, these same companies sell their products directly to consumers on Amazon, without any requirement for medical directors. This begs the question, why are they imposing such requirements on estheticians?

As a business owner, I believe in choosing companies that have ethical business practices. Companies that educate estheticians on their products and back them up. Brands like @furprofessionals, @elleebana, @starpilwaxusa, @lashandwaxoc, and @waxbarewax are a few examples of such companies that prioritize the well-being of estheticians.

While I am fortunate enough to work with brands that uphold ethical practices, I am aware that many estheticians are struggling due to the unethical practices of these skincare companies. It is time to demand change and support our esthie friends in their fight against such unfair practices.

It is essential to band together and raise awareness about such issues and use our voices to bring about a positive change in the industry. Let us choose to support brands that prioritize the well-being of estheticians and demand ethical practices from those who do not.

#aestheticianrevolution
